## Pre-PR Quality Gate

- [ ] All tests pass (`npm test`)
- [ ] Type check passes (`npm run check`)
- [ ] Linter passes (`npm run lint`)
- [ ] `/code-review --changed` passes
- [ ] Application works end-to-end in browser

## Risks & Open Questions

- **NFP for concave polygons is complex** — May need to simplify by convex-decomposing parts first. Can fall back to offset-based collision detection if NFP proves too difficult.
- **LightBurn format variations** — .lbrn (legacy XML) vs .lbrn2 (newer format) may differ. Need sample files to verify. May need to handle both formats.
- **Performance** — GA + NFP can be slow for many parts. Consider Web Workers for the optimizer to keep UI responsive.
- **Curve approximation fidelity** — Converting Bezier curves to line segments requires choosing a tolerance. Too few segments = inaccurate cuts; too many = slow nesting.
- **Free rotation search space** — Infinite rotation angles make GA search harder. Consider discretizing to e.g. 1° increments for practical performance.
